<specimenCount box="[1368,1399,1259,1283]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" type="female">1♀</specimenCount>
RTO). The interested reader will easilY realize its perfect match to the figures published bY 
<bibRefCitation author="ARMAS" box="[1098,1254,1323,1347]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="21 - 33" refId="ref2553" refString="ARMAS, L. F. DE. 1996. Presencia de Centruroides schmidti Sissom en el sureste de Mexico Y descripcion de dos especies nuevas (Scorpiones: Buthidae). Revista Nicaraguense de Entomologia, 36: 21 - 33." type="journal article" year="1996">Armas (1996)</bibRefCitation>
, Martín-Frías et al. (2005) and Santibáñez-López &amp; Ponce-Saavedra (2009) on one hand, and its absolute contradiction to those bY Goodman et al. (2021b) on the other.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[816,1475,234,1827]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
With respect to the infrageneric affiliation of the authentic 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Armas" authorityYear="1996" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Centruroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoffmanni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">C. hoffmanni</emphasis>
